{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"Tonight, I want to have a conversation about"},{"time":2995,"text":"this incredible global issue"},{"time":4929,"text":"that's at the intersection of land use, food and environment,"},{"time":9466,"text":"something we can all relate to,"},{"time":10787,"text":"and what I've been calling the other inconvenient truth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":13517,"text":"But first, I want to take you on a little journey."},{"time":16794,"text":"Let's first visit our planet, but at night,"},{"time":19590,"text":"and from space."},{"time":21126,"text":"This is what our planet looks like from outer space"},{"time":24077,"text":"at nighttime, if you were to take a satellite and travel"},{"time":26215,"text":"around the planet. And the thing you would notice first,"},{"time":29069,"text":"of course, is how dominant the human presence"},{"time":32386,"text":"on our planet is."},{"time":34450,"text":"We see cities, we see oil fields,"},{"time":37185,"text":"you can even make out fishing fleets in the sea,"},{"time":40382,"text":"that we are dominating much of our planet,"},{"time":42946,"text":"and mostly through the use of energy"},{"time":44719,"text":"that we see here at night."},{"time":46453,"text":"But let's go back and drop it a little deeper"},{"time":48627,"text":"and look during the daytime."},{"time":50669,"text":"What we see during the day is our landscapes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54359,"text":"This is part of the Amazon Basin, a place called Rond√¥nia"},{"time":57912,"text":"in the south-center part of the Brazilian Amazon."},{"time":61502,"text":"If you look really carefully in the upper right-hand corner,"},{"time":64118,"text":"you're going to see a thin white line,"},{"time":66644,"text":"which is a road that was built in the 1970s."},{"time":70022,"text":"If we come back to the same place in 2001,"},{"time":73689,"text":"what we're going to find is that these roads"},{"time":75946,"text":"spurt off more roads, and more roads after that,"},{"time":79796,"text":"at the end of which is a small clearing in the rainforest"},{"time":82937,"text":"where there are going to be a few cows."},{"time":85098,"text":"These cows are used for beef. We're going to eat these cows."},{"time":88410,"text":"And these cows are eaten basically in South America,"},{"time":91041,"text":"in Brazil and Argentina. They're not being shipped up here."},{"time":93825,"text":"But this kind of fishbone pattern of deforestation"},{"time":96561,"text":"is something we notice a lot of around the tropics,"},{"time":99146,"text":"especially in this part of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101374,"text":"If we go a little bit further south in our little tour of the world,"},{"time":104697,"text":"we can go to the Bolivian edge of the Amazon,"},{"time":107089,"text":"here also in 1975, and if you look really carefully,"},{"time":111225,"text":"there's a thin white line through that kind of seam,"},{"time":114787,"text":"and there's a lone farmer out there"},{"time":116099,"text":"in the middle of the primeval jungle."},{"time":118662,"text":"Let's come back again a few years later, here in 2003,"},{"time":123435,"text":"and we'll see that that landscape actually looks"},{"time":125963,"text":"a lot more like Iowa than it does like a rainforest."},{"time":128845,"text":"In fact, what you're seeing here are soybean fields."},{"time":132213,"text":"These soybeans are being shipped to Europe and to China"},{"time":135086,"text":"as animal feed, especially after the mad cow disease scare"},{"time":138832,"text":"about a decade ago, where we don't want to feed animals"},{"time":141373,"text":"animal protein anymore, because that can transmit disease."},{"time":144803,"text":"Instead, we want to feed them more vegetable proteins."},{"time":147415,"text":"So soybeans have really exploded,"},{"time":149207,"text":"showing how trade and globalization are"},{"time":152832,"text":"really responsible for the connections to rainforests"},{"time":155704,"text":"and the Amazon -- an incredibly strange"},{"time":157641,"text":"and interconnected world that we have today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160357,"text":"Well, again and again, what we find as we look"},{"time":162678,"text":"around the world in our little tour of the world"},{"time":164814,"text":"is that landscape after landscape after landscape"},{"time":168565,"text":"have been cleared and altered for growing food"},{"time":171334,"text":"and other crops."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173669,"text":"So one of the questions we've been asking is,"},{"time":176029,"text":"how much of the world is used to grow food,"},{"time":178517,"text":"and where is it exactly, and how can we change that"},{"time":180913,"text":"into the future, and what does it mean?"},{"time":183407,"text":"Well, our team has been looking at this on a global scale,"},{"time":186375,"text":"using satellite data and ground-based data kind of to track"},{"time":189295,"text":"farming on a global scale."},{"time":191479,"text":"And this is what we found, and it's startling."},{"time":195191,"text":"This map shows the presence of agriculture"},{"time":197982,"text":"on planet Earth."},{"time":200046,"text":"The green areas are the areas we use to grow crops,"},{"time":203006,"text":"like wheat or soybeans or corn or rice or whatever."},{"time":206207,"text":"That's 16 million square kilometers' worth of land."},{"time":210471,"text":"If you put it all together in one place,"},{"time":212595,"text":"it'd be the size of South America."},{"time":215262,"text":"The second area, in brown, is the world's pastures"},{"time":217938,"text":"and rangelands, where our animals live."},{"time":220155,"text":"That area's about 30 million square kilometers,"},{"time":222871,"text":"or about an Africa's worth of land,"},{"time":225290,"text":"a huge amount of land, and it's the best land, of course,"},{"time":228203,"text":"is what you see. And what's left is, like,"},{"time":230355,"text":"the middle of the Sahara Desert, or Siberia,"},{"time":232366,"text":"or the middle of a rain forest."},{"time":234057,"text":"We're using a planet's worth of land already."},{"time":237802,"text":"If we look at this carefully, we find it's about 40 percent"},{"time":240593,"text":"of the Earth's land surface is devoted to agriculture,"},{"time":243305,"text":"and it's 60 times larger"},{"time":245874,"text":"than all the areas we complain about,"},{"time":248449,"text":"our suburban sprawl and our cities where we mostly live."},{"time":251666,"text":"Half of humanity lives in cities today,"},{"time":254529,"text":"but a 60-times-larger area is used to grow food."},{"time":258465,"text":"So this is an amazing kind of result,"},{"time":260384,"text":"and it really shocked us when we looked at that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262561,"text":"So we're using an enormous amount of land for agriculture,"},{"time":265265,"text":"but also we're using a lot of water."},{"time":267971,"text":"This is a photograph flying into Arizona,"},{"time":270499,"text":"and when you look at it, you're like,"},{"time":271308,"text":"\"What are they growing here?\" It turns out"},{"time":272435,"text":"they're growing lettuce in the middle of the desert"},{"time":275367,"text":"using water sprayed on top."},{"time":277755,"text":"Now, the irony is, it's probably sold"},{"time":279305,"text":"in our supermarket shelves in the Twin Cities."},{"time":281981,"text":"But what's really interesting is, this water's got to come"},{"time":284293,"text":"from some place, and it comes from here,"},{"time":286837,"text":"the Colorado River in North America."},{"time":289477,"text":"Well, the Colorado on a typical day in the 1950s,"},{"time":292125,"text":"this is just, you know, not a flood, not a drought,"},{"time":294244,"text":"kind of an average day, it looks something like this."},{"time":297029,"text":"But if we come back today, during a normal condition"},{"time":299933,"text":"to the exact same location, this is what's left."},{"time":303501,"text":"The difference is mainly irrigating the desert for food,"},{"time":306503,"text":"or maybe golf courses in Scottsdale, you take your pick."},{"time":310059,"text":"Well, this is a lot of water, and again, we're mining water"},{"time":312979,"text":"and using it to grow food,"},{"time":315386,"text":"and today, if you travel down further down the Colorado,"},{"time":318066,"text":"it dries up completely and no longer flows into the ocean."},{"time":321346,"text":"We've literally consumed an entire river in North America"},{"time":324474,"text":"for irrigation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326602,"text":"Well, that's not even the worst example in the world."},{"time":328358,"text":"This probably is: the Aral Sea."},{"time":331178,"text":"Now, a lot you will remember this from your geography classes."},{"time":334082,"text":"This is in the former Soviet Union"},{"time":336141,"text":"in between Kazakhstan and Uzbekistan,"},{"time":338713,"text":"one of the great inland seas of the world."},{"time":341161,"text":"But there's kind of a paradox here, because it looks like"},{"time":343473,"text":"it's surrounded by desert. Why is this sea here?"},{"time":346995,"text":"The reason it's here is because, on the right-hand side,"},{"time":348958,"text":"you see two little rivers kind of coming down"},{"time":351450,"text":"through the sand, feeding this basin with water."},{"time":354967,"text":"Those rivers are draining snowmelt from mountains"},{"time":357549,"text":"far to the east, where snow melts, it travels down the river"},{"time":360482,"text":"through the desert, and forms the great Aral Sea."},{"time":363682,"text":"Well, in the 1950s, the Soviets decided to divert that water"},{"time":367694,"text":"to irrigate the desert to grow cotton, believe it or not,"},{"time":370047,"text":"in Kazakhstan, to sell cotton to the international markets"},{"time":373827,"text":"to bring foreign currency into the Soviet Union."},{"time":375887,"text":"They really needed the money."},{"time":377813,"text":"Well, you can imagine what happens. You turn off"},{"time":379809,"text":"the water supply to the Aral Sea, what's going to happen?"},{"time":382739,"text":"Here it is in 1973,"},{"time":385187,"text":"1986,"},{"time":387399,"text":"1999,"},{"time":390203,"text":"2004,"},{"time":393258,"text":"and about 11 months ago."},{"time":397923,"text":"It's pretty extraordinary."},{"time":399972,"text":"Now a lot of us in the audience here live in the Midwest."},{"time":403163,"text":"Imagine that was Lake Superior."},{"time":405823,"text":"Imagine that was Lake Huron."},{"time":409097,"text":"It's an extraordinary change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410704,"text":"This is not only a change in water and"},{"time":413047,"text":"where the shoreline is, this is a change in the fundamentals"},{"time":415416,"text":"of the environment of this region."},{"time":417673,"text":"Let's start with this."},{"time":418957,"text":"The Soviet Union didn't really have a Sierra Club."},{"time":421167,"text":"Let's put it that way."},{"time":422707,"text":"So what you find in the bottom of the Aral Sea ain't pretty."},{"time":426111,"text":"There's a lot of toxic waste, a lot of things"},{"time":428055,"text":"that were dumped there that are now becoming airborne."},{"time":430471,"text":"One of those small islands that was remote"},{"time":432603,"text":"and impossible to get to was a site"},{"time":434215,"text":"of Soviet biological weapons testing."},{"time":436911,"text":"You can walk there today."},{"time":438265,"text":"Weather patterns have changed."},{"time":439812,"text":"Nineteen of the unique 20 fish species found only"},{"time":443121,"text":"in the Aral Sea are now wiped off the face of the Earth."},{"time":446071,"text":"This is an environmental disaster writ large."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448951,"text":"But let's bring it home."},{"time":450446,"text":"This is a picture that Al Gore gave me a few years ago"},{"time":453175,"text":"that he took when he was in the Soviet Union"},{"time":454824,"text":"a long, long time ago,"},{"time":456086,"text":"showing the fishing fleets of the Aral Sea."},{"time":459082,"text":"You see the canal they dug?"},{"time":461240,"text":"They were so desperate to try to, kind of, float the boats into"},{"time":463704,"text":"the remaining pools of water, but they finally had to give up"},{"time":465920,"text":"because the piers and the moorings simply couldn't"},{"time":468384,"text":"keep up with the retreating shoreline."},{"time":470554,"text":"I don't know about you, but I'm terrified that future"},{"time":472565,"text":"archaeologists will dig this up and write stories about"},{"time":474963,"text":"our time in history, and wonder, \"What were you thinking?\""},{"time":477783,"text":"Well, that's the future we have to look forward to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480811,"text":"We already use about 50 percent of the Earth's fresh water"},{"time":483724,"text":"that's sustainable, and agriculture alone"},{"time":485916,"text":"is 70 percent of that."},{"time":488316,"text":"So we use a lot of water, a lot of land for agriculture."},{"time":491476,"text":"We also use a lot of the atmosphere for agriculture."},{"time":494820,"text":"Usually when we think about the atmosphere,"},{"time":497156,"text":"we think about climate change and greenhouse gases,"},{"time":499804,"text":"and mostly around energy,"},{"time":501860,"text":"but it turns out agriculture is one of the biggest emitters"},{"time":504496,"text":"of greenhouse gases too."},{"time":506548,"text":"If you look at carbon dioxide from"},{"time":508604,"text":"burning tropical rainforest,"},{"time":510756,"text":"or methane coming from cows and rice,"},{"time":513316,"text":"or nitrous oxide from too many fertilizers,"},{"time":516229,"text":"it turns out agriculture is 30 percent of the greenhouse"},{"time":519000,"text":"gases going into the atmosphere from human activity."},{"time":522016,"text":"That's more than all our transportation."},{"time":523870,"text":"It's more than all our electricity."},{"time":525620,"text":"It's more than all other manufacturing, in fact."},{"time":528245,"text":"It's the single largest emitter of greenhouse gases"},{"time":531355,"text":"of any human activity in the world."},{"time":533675,"text":"And yet, we don't talk about it very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":536301,"text":"So we have this incredible presence today of agriculture"},{"time":539354,"text":"dominating our planet,"},{"time":541491,"text":"whether it's 40 percent of our land surface,"},{"time":543849,"text":"70 percent of the water we use,"},{"time":545957,"text":"30 percent of our greenhouse gas emissions."},{"time":548682,"text":"We've doubled the flows of nitrogen and phosphorus"},{"time":551531,"text":"around the world simply by using fertilizers,"},{"time":553994,"text":"causing huge problems of water quality from rivers,"},{"time":556765,"text":"lakes, and even oceans, and it's also the single biggest"},{"time":559482,"text":"driver of biodiversity loss."},{"time":562157,"text":"So without a doubt, agriculture is"},{"time":564258,"text":"the single most powerful force unleashed on this planet"},{"time":567938,"text":"since the end of the ice age. No question."},{"time":570557,"text":"And it rivals climate change in importance."},{"time":573537,"text":"And they're both happening at the same time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":576462,"text":"But what's really important here to remember is that"},{"time":578834,"text":"it's not all bad. It's not that agriculture's a bad thing."},{"time":582102,"text":"In fact, we completely depend on it."},{"time":584282,"text":"It's not optional. It's not a luxury. It's an absolute necessity."},{"time":588722,"text":"We have to provide food and feed and, yeah,"},{"time":590866,"text":"fiber and even biofuels to something like seven billion people"},{"time":594722,"text":"in the world today, and if anything,"},{"time":597458,"text":"we're going to have the demands on agriculture"},{"time":599488,"text":"increase into the future. It's not going to go away."},{"time":602026,"text":"It's going to get a lot bigger, mainly because of"},{"time":604257,"text":"growing population. We're seven billion people today"},{"time":607250,"text":"heading towards at least nine,"},{"time":609450,"text":"probably nine and a half before we're done."},{"time":612242,"text":"More importantly, changing diets."},{"time":614619,"text":"As the world becomes wealthier as well as more populous,"},{"time":617666,"text":"we're seeing increases in dietary consumption of meat,"},{"time":620733,"text":"which take a lot more resources than a vegetarian diet does."},{"time":624194,"text":"So more people, eating more stuff, and richer stuff,"},{"time":628116,"text":"and of course having an energy crisis at the same time,"},{"time":631317,"text":"where we have to replace oil with other energy sources"},{"time":634790,"text":"that will ultimately have to include some kinds of biofuels"},{"time":637361,"text":"and bio-energy sources."},{"time":639140,"text":"So you put these together. It's really hard to see"},{"time":641893,"text":"how we're going to get to the rest of the century"},{"time":644245,"text":"without at least doubling global agricultural production."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648573,"text":"Well, how are we going to do this? How are going to"},{"time":650522,"text":"double global ag production around the world?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":653315,"text":"Well, we could try to farm more land."},{"time":656003,"text":"This is an analysis we've done, where on the left is where"},{"time":658802,"text":"the crops are today, on the right is where they could be"},{"time":662296,"text":"based on soils and climate, assuming climate change"},{"time":665244,"text":"doesn't disrupt too much of this,"},{"time":667085,"text":"which is not a good assumption."},{"time":668973,"text":"We could farm more land, but the problem is"},{"time":671162,"text":"the remaining lands are in sensitive areas."},{"time":674143,"text":"They have a lot of biodiversity, a lot of carbon,"},{"time":676181,"text":"things we want to protect."},{"time":678615,"text":"So we could grow more food by expanding farmland,"},{"time":681439,"text":"but we'd better not,"},{"time":682757,"text":"because it's ecologically a very, very dangerous thing to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":686423,"text":"Instead, we maybe want to freeze the footprint"},{"time":688807,"text":"of agriculture and farm the lands we have better."},{"time":692592,"text":"This is work that we're doing to try to highlight places"},{"time":694992,"text":"in the world where we could improve yields"},{"time":697559,"text":"without harming the environment."},{"time":699825,"text":"The green areas here show where corn yields,"},{"time":702226,"text":"just showing corn as an example,"},{"time":704376,"text":"are already really high, probably the maximum you could"},{"time":706977,"text":"find on Earth today for that climate and soil,"},{"time":709855,"text":"but the brown areas and yellow areas are places where"},{"time":712206,"text":"we're only getting maybe 20 or 30 percent of the yield"},{"time":714720,"text":"you should be able to get."},{"time":716060,"text":"You see a lot of this in Africa, even Latin America,"},{"time":718378,"text":"but interestingly, Eastern Europe, where Soviet Union"},{"time":721238,"text":"and Eastern Bloc countries used to be,"},{"time":723479,"text":"is still a mess agriculturally."},{"time":725703,"text":"Now, this would require nutrients and water."},{"time":728336,"text":"It's going to either be organic or conventional"},{"time":730469,"text":"or some mix of the two to deliver that."},{"time":732282,"text":"Plants need water and nutrients."},{"time":734447,"text":"But we can do this, and there are opportunities to make this work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":737655,"text":"But we have to do it in a way that is sensitive"},{"time":739935,"text":"to meeting the food security needs of the future"},{"time":742544,"text":"and the environmental security needs of the future."},{"time":745807,"text":"We have to figure out how to make this tradeoff between"},{"time":748821,"text":"growing food and having a healthy environment work better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752530,"text":"Right now, it's kind of an all-or-nothing proposition."},{"time":755060,"text":"We can grow food in the background --"},{"time":757022,"text":"that's a soybean field ‚Äî"},{"time":758483,"text":"and in this flower diagram, it shows we grow a lot of food,"},{"time":761610,"text":"but we don't have a lot clean water, we're not storing"},{"time":764128,"text":"a lot of carbon, we don't have a lot of biodiversity."},{"time":767125,"text":"In the foreground, we have this prairie"},{"time":769133,"text":"that's wonderful from the environmental side,"},{"time":770691,"text":"but you can't eat anything. What's there to eat?"},{"time":773895,"text":"We need to figure out how to bring both of those together"},{"time":776432,"text":"into a new kind of agriculture that brings them all together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":780542,"text":"Now, when I talk about this, people often tell me,"},{"time":782753,"text":"\"Well, isn't blank the answer?\" -- organic food,"},{"time":785985,"text":"local food, GMOs, new trade subsidies, new farm bills --"},{"time":790733,"text":"and yeah, we have a lot of good ideas here,"},{"time":793500,"text":"but not any one of these is a silver bullet."},{"time":796573,"text":"In fact, what I think they are is more like silver buckshot."},{"time":799533,"text":"And I love silver buckshot. You put it together"},{"time":802045,"text":"and you've got something really powerful,"},{"time":804363,"text":"but we need to put them together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":806763,"text":"So what we have to do, I think, is invent a new kind"},{"time":809296,"text":"of agriculture that blends the best ideas"},{"time":811980,"text":"of commercial agriculture and the green revolution"},{"time":815085,"text":"with the best ideas of organic farming and local food"},{"time":818637,"text":"and the best ideas of environmental conservation,"},{"time":822045,"text":"not to have them fighting each other but to have them"},{"time":823850,"text":"collaborating together to form a new kind of agriculture,"},{"time":827599,"text":"something I call \"terraculture,\" or farming for a whole planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":832317,"text":"Now, having this conversation has been really hard,"},{"time":835301,"text":"and we've been trying very hard to bring these key points"},{"time":837413,"text":"to people to reduce the controversy,"},{"time":839716,"text":"to increase the collaboration."},{"time":841216,"text":"I want to show you a short video that does kind of show"},{"time":843763,"text":"our efforts right now to bring these sides together"},{"time":846093,"text":"into a single conversation. So let me show you that."},{"time":849819,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":853480,"text":"(\"Institute on the Environment, University of Minnesota: Driven to Discover\")"},{"time":857137,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":858578,"text":"(\"The world population is growing"},{"time":860226,"text":"by 75 million people each year."},{"time":863239,"text":"That's almost the size of Germany."},{"time":865672,"text":"Today, we're nearing 7 billion people."},{"time":868615,"text":"At this rate, we'll reach 9 billion people by 2040."},{"time":871305,"text":"And we all need food."},{"time":873073,"text":"But how?"},{"time":874424,"text":"How do we feed a growing world without destroying the planet?"},{"time":877312,"text":"We already know climate change is a big problem."},{"time":880557,"text":"But it's not the only problem."},{"time":881807,"text":"We need to face 'the other inconvenient truth.'"},{"time":884729,"text":"A global crisis in agriculture."},{"time":887277,"text":"Population growth + meat consumption + dairy consumption + energy costs + bioenergy production = stress on natural resources."},{"time":893536,"text":"More than 40% of Earth's land has been cleared for agriculture."},{"time":896985,"text":"Global croplands cover 16 million km¬≤."},{"time":898991,"text":"That's almost the size of South America."},{"time":902184,"text":"Global pastures cover 30 million km¬≤."},{"time":903979,"text":"That's the size of Africa."},{"time":906054,"text":"Agriculture uses 60 times more land than urban and suburban areas combined."},{"time":910770,"text":"Irrigation is the biggest use of water on the planet."},{"time":914482,"text":"We use 2,800 cubic kilometers of water on crops every year."},{"time":918856,"text":"That's enough to fill 7,305 Empire State Buildings every day."},{"time":922638,"text":"Today, many large rivers have reduced flows."},{"time":925619,"text":"Some dry up altogether."},{"time":927643,"text":"Look at the Aral Sea, now turned to desert."},{"time":931627,"text":"Or the Colorado River, which no longer flows to the ocean."},{"time":935250,"text":"Fertilizers have more than doubled the phosphorus and nitrogen in the environment."},{"time":939133,"text":"The consequence?"},{"time":940389,"text":"Widespread water pollution"},{"time":942373,"text":"and massive degradation of lakes and rivers."},{"time":944535,"text":"Surprisingly, agriculture is the biggest contributor to climate change."},{"time":948909,"text":"It generates 30% of greenhouse gas emissions."},{"time":951336,"text":"That's more than the emissions from all electricity and industry,"},{"time":954029,"text":"or from all the world's planes, trains and automobiles."},{"time":957005,"text":"Most agricultural emissions come from tropical deforestation,"},{"time":959373,"text":"methane from animals and rice fields,"},{"time":960749,"text":"and nitrous oxide from over-fertilizing."},{"time":962581,"text":"There is nothing we do that transforms the world more than agriculture."},{"time":965836,"text":"And there's nothing we do that is more crucial to our survival."},{"time":969367,"text":"Here's the dilemma..."},{"time":970873,"text":"As the world grows by several billion more people,"},{"time":975228,"text":"We'll need to double, maybe even triple, global food production."},{"time":979812,"text":"So where do we go from here?"},{"time":981208,"text":"We need a bigger conversation, an international dialogue."},{"time":984011,"text":"We need to invest in real solutions:"},{"time":985819,"text":"incentives for farmers, precision agriculture, new crop varieties, drip irrigation,"},{"time":990157,"text":"gray water recycling, better tillage practices, smarter diets."},{"time":993818,"text":"We need everyone at the table."},{"time":996024,"text":"Advocates of commercial agriculture,"},{"time":997974,"text":"environmental conservation,"},{"time":999121,"text":"and organic farming..."},{"time":1000582,"text":"must work together."},{"time":1002617,"text":"There is no single solution."},{"time":1004191,"text":"We need collaboration,"},{"time":1005800,"text":"imagination,"},{"time":1007236,"text":"determination,"},{"time":1008014,"text":"because failure is not an option."},{"time":1011673,"text":"How do we feed the world without destroying it?"},{"time":1015370,"text":"Yeah, so we face one of the greatest grand challenges"},{"time":1018236,"text":"in all of human history today:"},{"time":1020346,"text":"the need to feed nine billion people"},{"time":1023020,"text":"and do so sustainably and equitably and justly,"},{"time":1026774,"text":"at the same time protecting our planet"},{"time":1028475,"text":"for this and future generations."},{"time":1031288,"text":"This is going to be one of the hardest things"},{"time":1032804,"text":"we ever have done in human history,"},{"time":1034675,"text":"and we absolutely have to get it right,"},{"time":1037925,"text":"and we have to get it right on our first and only try."},{"time":1042262,"text":"So thanks very much. (Applause)"}]}]}